<item>
            <title>[BEAM-6460] Jackson Cache may hold on to Classloader after pipeline restart</title>
                <link>https://issues.apache.org/jira/browse/BEAM-6460</link>
                <project id="12319527" key="BEAM">Beam</project>
                    <description>&lt;p&gt;It looks like Jackson has an internal cache which may continue to hold the Flink application classloader through its &lt;tt&gt;TypeFactory&lt;/tt&gt; class. When the pipeline is restarted due to a failure, a new classloader is created which can result in too many classes being loaded.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;Reported on the user mailing list: &lt;a href=&quot;https://lists.apache.org/thread.html/e201891684ef3dcffce48d20d1f9be0e19fc2294334362cc7092c0ff@%3Cuser.beam.apache.org%3E&quot; class=&quot;external-link&quot; target=&quot;_blank&quot; rel=&quot;nofollow noopener&quot;&gt;https://lists.apache.org/thread.html/e201891684ef3dcffce48d20d1f9be0e19fc2294334362cc7092c0ff@%3Cuser.beam.apache.org%3E&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/p&gt;</description>
